00:54:07,576 --> 00:54:11,333
I think the people who got involved
in the counterculture

800
00:54:11,461 --> 00:54:14,421
perceived that they did not want
to be a part

801
00:54:14,545 --> 00:54:18,302
of what was wrong with a culture
that was destroying the world.

802
00:54:18,428 --> 00:54:22,390
I can see that much better in
retrospect than I could right then.

803
00:54:22,513 --> 00:54:28,388
But the point is that it was
the culture that was sick.

804
00:54:28,520 --> 00:54:34,361
It was the whole American way
of looking at things that was sick.

805
00:54:34,486 --> 00:54:38,243
So I think we came to a realisation
that one way to change that

806
00:54:38,370 --> 00:54:40,327
is to just live it differently.

807
00:54:40,453 --> 00:54:43,208
lnstead of trying
to change the structure

808
00:54:43,336 --> 00:54:45,373
in a direct confrontational way,

809
00:54:45,497 --> 00:54:50,131
you just drop out and live it
the way you think it ought to be.

810
00:54:51,104 --> 00:54:53,665
Do you play anything
besides a sweet potato?

811
00:54:53,787 --> 00:54:57,942
Just the drums and the trumpet.

812
00:54:58,071 --> 00:55:01,429
Yeah, and I go up in the mountains
and yell now and then.

813
00:55:01,555 --> 00:55:04,674
- You do what?
- Go up in the mountains and yell.

814
00:55:04,799 --> 00:55:07,759
Way up high in the mountains
and yell as hard as I can.

815
00:55:07,882 --> 00:55:10,637
- What's the purpose of that?
- To greet the dawn

816
00:55:10,765 --> 00:55:14,443
and the greet the noonday sun
and to greet the sunset.

817
00:55:14,569 --> 00:55:17,529
You stay all day
yelling at morning, noon and night?

818
00:55:17,653 --> 00:55:21,011
Right. And standing on my head
and making gardens

819
00:55:21,137 --> 00:55:22,695
and painting pictures.

820
00:55:22,819 --> 00:55:25,574
You not only play the sweet potato,
you also grow them?

821
00:55:25,701 --> 00:55:27,259
Right.

822
00:55:28,424 --> 00:55:35,701
Why do you indulge in smoking
this... these narcotic cigarettes?

823
00:55:35,833 --> 00:55:37,586
Why do people drink alcohol?

824
00:55:38,955 --> 00:55:41,915
- lt's the same reason.
- lt's a big Ping-Pong table.

825
00:55:42,039 --> 00:55:44,999
You say why do we do this
and we say, ''Why do you do this?''

826
00:55:45,122 --> 00:55:48,879
We don't agree... You're the mess.
We're trying to change it.

827
00:55:49,007 --> 00:55:51,363
Why? What are you trying
to change it to?

828
00:55:51,489 --> 00:55:53,845
What are your principles?
Do you have any?

829
00:55:53,972 --> 00:55:58,287
We're not trying to change anything.
We're just trying to be ourselves

830
00:55:58,417 --> 00:56:02,129
- and do what we think is right.
- Why don't you go out in the desert

831
00:56:02,261 --> 00:56:04,298
instead of dirtying up a community?

832
00:56:04,423 --> 00:56:06,415
We're not dirtying up anything.

833
00:56:08,788 --> 00:56:14,265
My parents sent away to the Bay Area
a serious young folk singer.

834
00:56:14,394 --> 00:56:17,149
I came back with long hair
down to there.

835
00:56:17,277 --> 00:56:21,239
I was wearing an enormous
amount of beads around my neck.

836
00:56:21,361 --> 00:56:25,403
They figured I had abandoned
everything I was taught.

837
00:56:25,526 --> 00:56:27,677
I realised...

838
00:56:28,650 --> 00:56:30,881
We had big arguments
about this stuff.

839
00:56:31,012 --> 00:56:35,293
I tried to convince them to sell
their furniture and go to lndia.

840
00:56:35,417 --> 00:56:37,886
And they weren't going for it.

841
00:56:38,420 --> 00:56:42,177
I realised that no matter how far out
their political views were,

842
00:56:42,305 --> 00:56:45,219
because they were mighty unpopular,

843
00:56:45,347 --> 00:56:48,421
my parents were pretty left wing,

844
00:56:48,551 --> 00:56:52,992
that really they were materialists.

845
00:56:53,116 --> 00:56:56,474
They were concerned about
how the wealth was divided up.

846
00:56:56,599 --> 00:57:00,641
At that point, in my consciousness,
I didn't care about wealth.

847
00:57:00,764 --> 00:57:03,758
We were actually living communally,

848
00:57:03,888 --> 00:57:07,679
rather than talking about communism.

